name: scljet-sql-modulo
description: SclJet SQL % modulo operator — integer modulo, multiplicative precedence, in projection and WHERE; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL `%` modulo

`a % b` is integer modulo (operands converted to integers, result truncates toward zero, `x % 0` =
NULL), at the same precedence as `* /`. It works in the projection (`n % 3`, `n % 3 + 1`, `20 % n`)
and in `WHERE` (`WHERE n % 2 = 0`). Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the
same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "nums", "CREATE TABLE nums(id INTEGER, n INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlInteger(7L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlInteger(15L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlInteger(8L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlInteger(3L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, n % 3 FROM nums")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM nums WHERE n % 2 = 0")
    show(db, "SELECT id, n % 3 + 1 FROM nums")
    show(db, "SELECT id, 20 % n FROM nums")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM nums WHERE n % 5 = 0")
```
